#
# Config.in — Kconfig entry for the netblink package
#

config BR2_PACKAGE_NETBLINK
bool "netblink"
default n
help
  A minimal Linux command-line utility that monitors network
  connectivity or traffic and indicates status via a GPIO-driven
  LED using the sysfs interface.

  Two modes are supported:
    ping     — periodically ping a host; blink LED based on RTT.
    traffic  — monitor interface tx+rx; blink LED based on rate.

  Usage:
    netblink <gpio> ping <host> [interval_sec [timeout_sec]]
    netblink <gpio> traffic [interface]

  https://openipc.org
